SIMPLE: issuable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Issuable
<hw>Is"su*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Issue</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Leading to, producing, or relating to, an issue;
capable of being made an issue at law.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lawful or suitable to be issued; <as>as, a writ
<ex>issuable</ex> on these grounds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Issuable plea</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a plea to
the merits, on which the adverse party may take issue and proceed to
trial.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Issuably</ent>⟦br⟧
